wiki_overview.content:
<blog>

# Fahim Kamal Ahmed - Game Developer Portfolio

## Project Introduction

### Purpose Statement
This is a modern, responsive portfolio website showcasing the professional work and personal projects of Fahim Kamal Ahmed, a Game Developer and Level Designer specializing in Unreal Engine and Unity. The portfolio serves as a digital showcase for his 3+ years of experience in game development, level design, and game production.

### Core Goals and Objectives
- **Professional Showcase**: Present both personal and professional game development projects in an organized, visually appealing manner
- **Interactive Experience**: Provide seamless navigation between project cards and detailed project pages
- **Modern Web Standards**: Demonstrate proficiency with contemporary web technologies including React, TypeScript, and Vite
- **Performance Optimization**: Ensure fast loading times and smooth scrolling experiences across all devices

### Target Audience
- Potential employers and clients seeking game development talent
- Industry professionals networking and collaboration opportunities
- Educational institutions and recruiters evaluating candidate profiles
- Gaming enthusiasts interested in game development processes and techniques

## Technical Architecture

### Component Breakdown
The portfolio follows a modular React architecture with clear separation of concerns:

```mermaid
graph TD
    App[App Component] --> Router[React Router]
    Router --> Home[Home Page]
    Router --> ProjectDetail[Project Detail Page]
    
    Home --> Navbar[Navigation Bar]
    Home --> Hero[Hero Section]
    Home --> Projects[Projects Section]
    Home --> About[About Section]
    Home --> Journey[Journey Section]
    Home --> Footer[Footer]
    
    Projects --> ProjectCard[Individual Project Cards]
    ProjectDetail --> ProjectContent[Detailed Project Content]
    
    ProjectCard --> ProjectLinks[External Links]
    ProjectContent --> SectionComponents[Dynamic Sections]
```

### Design Patterns
- **Component Composition**: Reusable UI components with consistent props interfaces
- **Data-Driven Rendering**: Project data stored in TypeScript interfaces for type safety
- **Responsive Design**: Mobile-first approach with Tailwind CSS utility classes
- **State Management**: Minimal state with React hooks for interactive elements

### System Relationships
```mermaid
flowchart TD
    Browser[Web Browser] --> React[React Application]
    React --> Router[React Router DOM]
    Router --> Components[UI Components]
    Components --> Data[Project Data]
    Data --> API[Static Data Files]
    
    Components --> Icons[Lucide React Icons]
    Components --> Styling[Tailwind CSS]
    Components --> Animation[Smooth Scrolling]
```

### Data Flow
```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant Router
    participant Home
    participant Projects
    participant ProjectDetail
    
    User->>Router: Navigate to "/"
    Router->>Home: Render Home Component
    Home->>Projects: Load Project Data
    Projects->>ProjectDetail: Route to Project Details
    ProjectDetail->>User: Display Detailed Content
```

## Key Implementation

### Main Entry Points
- **Application Root**: `src/main.tsx` - Initializes React application with strict mode
- **Routing Configuration**: `src/App.tsx` - Sets up React Router with scroll-to-top functionality
- **HTML Template**: `index.html` - Provides SEO metadata and base HTML structure

### Core Modules
- **Project Data Management**: `src/data/projects.ts` - Centralized project data with TypeScript interfaces
- **Page Components**: `src/pages/Home.tsx`, `src/pages/ProjectDetail.tsx` - Main page layouts
- **UI Components**: `src/components/` - Reusable component library (Navbar, Hero, Projects, etc.)
- **Styling System**: `src/index.css` - Custom CSS variables and Tailwind configuration

### Configuration Approach
- **Build System**: `vite.config.ts` - Vite configuration with React and Tailwind plugins
- **TypeScript Setup**: `tsconfig.json` - Multi-config TypeScript setup
- **Package Management**: `package.json` - Dependencies including React, React Router, and development tools

### External Dependencies
- **Runtime Dependencies**: React 19.2.0, React DOM 19.2.0, React Router DOM 7.13.0, Lucide React 0.563.0
- **Development Dependencies**: Vite 7.2.4, TypeScript ~5.9.3, Tailwind CSS 4.1.18, ESLint 9.39.1
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4.1.18 with custom color scheme and typography

### Integration Points
- **Icon System**: Lucide React provides consistent iconography across the application
- **Routing**: React Router DOM handles client-side navigation between pages
- **State Management**: React hooks for interactive elements like mobile navigation and scroll effects

### Component Relationship Diagram
```mermaid
graph LR
    App[App] --> Home[Home Page]
    App --> ProjectDetail[Project Detail]
    
    Home --> Navbar[Navigation]
    Home --> Hero[Hero Section]
    Home --> Projects[Projects Grid]
    Home --> About[About Me]
    Home --> Journey[Experience]
    Home --> Footer[Footer]
    
    Projects --> ProjectCard[Individual Cards]
    ProjectDetail --> ProjectContent[Detailed Content]
    
    ProjectCard --> Links[External Links]
    ProjectContent --> Sections[Dynamic Sections]
```

## Key Features

### Functionality Overview
- **Single Page Application**: Seamless navigation without page reloads
- **Responsive Design**: Mobile-first approach with adaptive layouts
- **Smooth Scrolling**: Automatic scroll-to-top on route changes
- **Project Filtering**: Separate sections for personal and professional projects
- **Rich Media Display**: Image galleries and interactive project cards

### Implementation Highlights
- **Dynamic Project Rendering**: `src/pages/ProjectDetail.tsx` - Creates detailed project pages from structured data
- **Mobile Navigation**: `src/components/Navbar.tsx` - Collapsible navigation with scroll-aware styling
- **Project Gallery**: `src/components/Projects.tsx` - Responsive grid layout with hover effects
- **Hero Section**: `src/components/Hero.tsx` - Feature-rich introduction with capability highlights

### Feature Architecture
```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> HomePage: User visits /
    HomePage --> ProjectCards: View projects
    ProjectCards --> ProjectDetail: Click project card
    ProjectDetail --> HomePage: Back to home
    ProjectDetail --> ExternalLink: Visit GitHub/Play Store
    ExternalLink --> ProjectDetail: Return to project
    
    HomePage --> AboutSection: Scroll to About
    HomePage --> ContactSection: Scroll to Contact
    HomePage --> ResumeDownload: Download resume
    
    AboutSection --> HomePage: Back to home
    ContactSection --> HomePage: Back to home
    ResumeDownload --> HomePage: Back to home
```

### Performance Considerations
- **Lazy Loading**: Images use `loading="lazy"` attribute for improved performance
- **CSS-in-JS**: Tailwind CSS provides efficient styling with minimal bundle size
- **Minimal Dependencies**: Lightweight dependency stack focused on core functionality
- **Optimized Routing**: Client-side routing eliminates server requests for navigation

---

**Sources:**
- [package.json](package.json)
- [App.tsx](src/App.tsx)
- [main.tsx](src/main.tsx)
- [Home.tsx](src/pages/Home.tsx)
- [ProjectDetail.tsx](src/pages/ProjectDetail.tsx)
- [projects.ts](src/data/projects.ts)
- [Projects.tsx](src/components/Projects.tsx)
- [Navbar.tsx](src/components/Navbar.tsx)
- [Hero.tsx](src/components/Hero.tsx)
- [index.css](src/index.css)
- [vite.config.ts](vite.config.ts)
- [index.html](index.html)
- [tsconfig.json](tsconfig.json)

</blog>
